 Burna Boy has set new records as the first African musician to headline a concert at the Madison Square Garden in New York, and the first Nigerian singer to sell out all the tickets for the venue. The musician will hold his first-ever concert tagged ‘One Night In Space’, on Thursday, April 28, 2022, in celebration of his international audience. To make the moment more historic, Burna Boy has planned to livestream the ‘One Night In Space’, which will be presented by YouTube at 9 p.m. ET on the day of the show. Burna Boy aims at capturing the ‘larger than life’ excitement and performance of the show that he designed to showcase in the city. The world’s most famous arena, Madison Square Garden, is a 20, 789 multi-purpose indoor arena in New York City.